    "what_description": "Salvia karelinii is a perennial herbaceous plant belonging to the family Lamiaceae. It has erect stems that grow up to 60-120 cm tall, with a woody base and a branched, leafy upper part. The leaves are opposite, ovate to lanceolate in shape, and measure 6-12 cm long by 2-4 cm wide. The leaves are covered in dense, grayish tomentum, which helps to repel herbivores and reduce transpiration. The plant produces terminal spikes of blue, tubular flowers, with a four-lobed calyx and a two-lipped corolla, from July to September.",
