    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Salvia karelinii are its antimicrobial activity, which prevents the growth of various pathogens, including bacteria and fungi. The antioxidant activity of Salvia karelinii protects cells from oxidative damage, and its anti-inflammatory properties reduce swelling and pain by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. The neuroprotective effects of Salvia karelinii may be attributed to the ability of its bioactive compounds to reduce oxidative stress and inhibit neurodegenerative processes, while its antispasmodic properties alleviate muscle spasms by relaxing smooth muscle tissues. The plant's bioactive compounds, including flavonoids, phenolic acids, and diterpenes, are responsible for these medicinal properties. These bioactive compounds work synergistically to exhibit the diverse therapeutic properties of Salvia karelinii.",
