    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Salvia karelinii are rosmarinic acid, quercetin, salvianolic acid b, carnosic acid, and luteolin, which possess potent antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. Rosmarinic acid and carnosic acid exhibit strong scavenging activity against free radicals, protecting cells from oxidative damage, while salvianolic acid b demonstrates significant inhibition of inflammatory mediators. Quercetin and luteolin also show anti-inflammatory activity, with quercetin inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and luteolin exerting antioxidant effects through the suppression of reactive oxygen species. The antioxidant capacity of these constituents is attributed to their ability to donate electrons and neutralize free radicals, thereby preventing cellular damage and promoting tissue repair. The combined action of these compounds contributes to the plant's therapeutic potential in treating various diseases, including oxidative stress-related disorders and inflammatory conditions.",
