    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Salvia karelinii improperly include experiencing hallucinations due to its ability to alter perception and induce intense visuals, developing psychosis in susceptible individuals due to its powerful psychoactive properties, exhibiting aggressive behavior as a result of the substance's ability to alter mood and increase irritability, experiencing panic attacks as a response to the intense and unpredictable effects of the substance, and these side effects are particularly concerning because Salvia karelinii can cause users to become detached from reality and lose control, which can lead to severe negative consequences.",
    "uses": "Salvia karelinii has been traditionally used in folk medicine to treat various ailments, including fever, respiratory issues, and gastrointestinal problems. Its medicinal properties are attributed to its bioactive compounds, such as alkaloids and phenolic acids. The plant is also believed to possess antibacterial and anti-inflammatory activities. In traditional medicine, Salvia karelinii is often used to treat symptoms of colds and flu. Additionally, it is sometimes used to treat digestive issues, such as diarrhea and dysentery.",
    "taxonomy": "Salvia karelinii is classified as a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae. It belongs to the genus Salvia, which is a group of plants commonly known as sages. The plant is native to the mountainous regions of Central Asia and is often found growing in rocky areas. Salvia karelinii is a perennial herb, producing blue-purple flowers in late spring and early summer. Its classification also places it within the order Lamiales.",
    "benefits": "Salvia karelinii is known for its potential health benefits, which include reducing inflammation and improving cognitive function. Its extracts have been studied for their antioxidant properties, which may help protect against cell damage and oxidative stress. Additionally, Salvia karelinii may help alleviate symptoms of anxiety and insomnia due to its sedative effects. The plant's active compounds have also been found to have antimicrobial properties, which could aid in wound healing and preventing infections. Further research is needed to fully understand the extent of Salvia karelinii's health benefits.",
    "parts": "Salvia karelinii is a plant species known for its medicinal properties, particularly in traditional medicine. The leaves of Salvia karelinii are considered the medicinal part, used to treat various health issues. The leaves contain compounds such as flavonoids and phenolic acids, which are believed to contribute to their medicinal effects. The plant is traditionally used to treat conditions like fever, respiratory issues, and gastrointestinal problems. Further research is needed to fully understand the medicinal properties and potential applications of Salvia karelinii.",
    "intro": "Salvia karelinii, also known as Sarygash, is a perennial plant belonging to the Lamiaceae family, native to Central Asia and Kazakhstan. The plant is valued for its medicinal properties, offering health benefits such as reduced inflammation, improved memory, and antioxidant activity. The bioactive constituents of Salvia karelinii include neuroprotective compounds like salvinorin A, flavonoids, and phenolic acids, which contribute to its therapeutic effects. Salvia karelinii is commonly used in traditional medicine, and is often prepared as a tea or tincture, as well as being used in the form of capsules or extracts for its health-promoting properties."
